data: Malcolm P. Savedoff Professor of Astronomy, Emeritus PhD in Physics, Princeton University, 1951 206 Bausch & Lomb Hall Fax: (585) 273-3237 msavedof@ur.rochester.edu Research Overview Professor Savedoff's research is in the area of theoretical astrophysics . He has been primarily concerned with stellar interiors, with the interstellar medium, and with hydrodynamics on cosmic scales.
